        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(claude-cli): surface re-auth hint when subprocess OAuth token expires",
        "body": "Fixes #97553\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `claude-cli/*` is the active model and Claude CLI's stored OAuth token has expired, the user receives:\n\n> ⚠️ Authentication failed (provider returned HTTP 401). Your provider token may have expired — try the request again in a moment. If the failure persists, re-authenticate this provider.\n\ninstead of the targeted re-auth hint:\n\n> ⚠️ Model login expired on the gateway for claude-cli. Re-auth with `openclaw models auth login --provider claude-cli`, then try again.\n\n## Root Cause (Two Gaps)\n\n**Gap 1 — `isOAuthRefreshFailureMessage` doesn't recognise the Claude subprocess 401 shape.**\n\nThe function only matched openclaw's own OAuth-refresh error strings.  When the `claude` subprocess has an expired token it emits:\n\n```\nFailed to authenticate. API Error: 401 Invalid authentication credentials\n```\n\nwrapped in a `FailoverError` whose message includes the `claude-cli` provider prefix.  None of the three existing patterns matched, so `classifyOAuthRefreshFailure` returned `null` and the re-auth hint was never reached.\n\n**Gap 2 — `classifyProviderRequestError` intercepts the `FailoverError` first.**\n\nBoth in `buildExternalRunFailureReply` _and_ in the `runAgentTurnWithFallback` catch block, `classifyProviderRequestError` ran before the OAuth-refresh check.  Its typed-401 branch (`reason:\"auth\" && status:401`) captured the `FailoverError` and emitted the generic provider-auth copy.\n\n## Fix\n\n**`src/agents/auth-profiles/oauth-refresh-failure.ts`**\n\n- Add `CLAUDE_CLI_AUTH_FAILURE_RE` regex matching messages that contain the `claude-cli` prefix and the subprocess 401 phrase.\n- `isClaudeCliExpiredOAuthMessage` helper (module-private) wraps the regex test.\n- `isOAuthRefreshFailureMessage` extended with the new helper.\n- `extractOAuthRefreshFailureProvider` returns `\"claude-cli\"` for the new pattern (no text-parsing needed; the provider is statically known).\n- `classifyOAuthRefreshFailureReason` maps the new pattern to `\"revoked\"` so the \"expired\" copy branch is taken.\n\n**`src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts`**\n\n- `buildExternalRunFailureReply`: move the `oauthRefreshFailure` block before `providerRequestError`.\n- `runAgentTurnWithFallback` catch block: guard the `providerRequestError` assignment so it is `undefined` when `classifyOAuthRefreshFailure` already matched the message.  This prevents the `FailoverError` typed-401 branch from short-circuiting before `buildExternalRunFailureReply` is reached.\n\n## Validation Evidence\n\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs   src/agents/auth-profiles/oauth-refresh-failure.test.ts   src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts\n```\n\n```\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  220 passed (220)   (4 + 216)\n```\n\nNew tests added:\n\n- `oauth-refresh-failure.test.ts`: \"classifies claude-cli subprocess 401 OAuth expiry as a provider refresh failure\" + negative control for non-claude-cli 401.\n- `agent-runner-execution.test.ts`: \"surfaces claude-cli re-auth hint over generic provider auth copy for 401 OAuth expiry\" — exercises the full `runAgentTurnWithFallback` path with a real `FailoverError{reason:\"auth\", status:401, provider:\"claude-cli\"}`.\n\n## Security & Privacy\n\nNo secrets, credentials, or user data are touched.  The new regex only reads the `claude-cli` provider id from the existing FailoverError message text to select the correct re-auth command; no external input is embedded in shell output.\n\n## Compatibility\n\nExisting OAuth refresh failure handling for all other providers is unchanged: the new `isClaudeCliExpiredOAuthMessage` guard requires the literal `\"claude-cli\"` substring, so unrelated provider 401 failures continue to reach `classifyProviderRequestError` as before.\n\n_AI-assisted (Claude Sonnet 4.6 + manual review and test validation)_",
        "branch": "fix/claude-cli-oauth-expiry-detection",
